#importing Pandas as pd
import pandas as pd

#importing the file excel
base = pd.read_csv("07. Pandas.csv")

#the type of our data base is DataFrame
type(base)

#by default, the head() call the first 5 lines
base.head()

#but we can call more lines, if we put the number inside of ( )
base.head(15)

#tail() by default call the last 5 lines
base.tail()

#size of our data base: 10 columns and 7100 lines
base.shape

#call the previous 3 information at once.: the 5 first lines, the 5 last lines and the DB size
display(base)

We will always have to follow these 3 steps
1. Import the Pandas: import Pandas the pd
2. Import base: base = pd.read_csv ('file name')
3. View the base: display(base)
